  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, net.sf.mmm.util.entity.api.Entity, net.sf.mmm.util.entity.api.GenericEntity<Long>, net.sf.mmm.util.entity.api.MutableGenericEntity<Long>, net.sf.mmm.util.entity.api.MutableRevisionedEntity<Long>, net.sf.mmm.util.entity.api.RevisionedEntity<Long>, net.sf.mmm.util.lang.api.attribute.AttributeReadId<Long>, net.sf.mmm.util.transferobject.api.TransferObject

    public abstract class AbstractEto
extends AbstractTo
implements net.sf.mmm.util.entity.api.MutableRevisionedEntity<Long>
    This is the abstract base class for an TransferObject that only contains data without relations. This is called DTO (data transfer object). Here data means properties that typically represent a net.sf.mmm.util.lang.api.Datatype and potentially for relations the ID (as Long). For actual relations you will use CTOs to express what set of entities to transfer, load, save, update, etc. without redundancies. It typically corresponds to an entity. For additional details and an example consult the package JavaDoc.

    hohwille, erandres
